 following props:"},"91":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-13","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#basic-usage","content":"The default carousel is a carousel that is uncontrolled, it shows the first slide by default. You can also pass the `defaultActiveIndex` prop to the `Carousel` component to set the initial active slide index."},"92":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-14","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#controlled","content":"The controlled carousel is a carousel that is controlled by the `activeIndex` prop."},"93":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-15","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#external-controls-uncontrolled","content":"You can control the carousel externally by passing the `ref` prop to the `Carousel` component and using the `emblaApi` to control the carousel imperatively."},"94":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-16","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#external-controls-controlled","content":"You can control the carousel externally by using the `activeIndex` prop to control the active slide index."},"95":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-17","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#hide-controls","content":"The hide controls carousel is a carousel that hides the navigation controls."},"96":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-18","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#variable-widths","content":"It supports multiple slides with different widths."},"97":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-19","page_id":"/docs/components/carousel","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/carousel#events","content":"You can listen to events like `onChange`, `onPrev`, or `onNext`."},"98":{"id":"/docs/components/carousel-20","page_id":"